WEBVTT

00:03.511 --> 00:06.111
Aw, man, did you see
this post from Raj?

00:06.113 --> 00:08.580
What? Is it another
video of him and his dog

00:08.582 --> 00:11.917
Lady-and-the-Tramping
some spaghetti?

00:11.919 --> 00:14.186
No. He can't afford
his apartment,

00:14.188 --> 00:17.122
and he's asking if anyone knows
of a cheap place to live.

00:17.124 --> 00:20.559
I want to say "India,"
but it seems mean.

00:23.230 --> 00:24.730
What's so funny?

00:24.732 --> 00:27.166
Raj is looking for
a cheap place to live,

00:27.168 --> 00:29.668
and I wrote "India."

00:29.670 --> 00:33.372
Don't post that;
be supportive.

00:33.374 --> 00:36.842
Maybe you should be supportive
of my hilarious jokes.

00:38.412 --> 00:40.646
Fine, what should we do?

00:40.648 --> 00:43.015
We're smart. I'm sure we
can think of something.

00:43.017 --> 00:44.550
You want to let him
live here?

00:44.552 --> 00:46.652
Oh, we're smarter
than that.

00:47.621 --> 00:49.922
I know our
apartment's small,

00:49.924 --> 00:51.890
but I think we
can make room.

00:51.892 --> 00:53.325
No, Sheldon.

00:53.327 --> 00:56.195
We are not getting
a life-size Spider-Man statue.

00:58.232 --> 01:00.866
We do have Sheldon's old room.

01:00.868 --> 01:02.334
If he really needs
a place to stay,

01:02.336 --> 01:03.936
I guess we should
offer it to him.

01:03.938 --> 01:05.236
You're a good friend.

01:05.239 --> 01:08.140
Am I still a good friend
if I wait and hope

01:08.142 --> 01:10.809
that Howard offers him
a place to live first?

01:10.811 --> 01:13.011
You're an even
better husband.

01:14.448 --> 01:16.715
I know if the roles
were reversed,

01:16.717 --> 01:18.617
he would do it for me.

01:18.619 --> 01:20.118
Where would he stay?

01:20.120 --> 01:21.620
We already have Stuart.

01:21.622 --> 01:24.489
Well, we can make some space
in the garage.

01:24.491 --> 01:26.525
Maybe put a cot out there,

01:26.527 --> 01:28.827
get him a space heater,
maybe a hot plate.

01:28.829 --> 01:30.329
That sounds awful.

01:30.331 --> 01:33.232
Let's hope he thinks so, too.

01:33.234 --> 01:35.200
For the last time,

01:35.202 --> 01:39.404
no Hulk, no Batman,
no life-size statues.

01:39.406 --> 01:41.940
Wow. I'm starting to
think you didn't mean it

01:41.942 --> 01:44.610
when you said you wanted
to spruce up the place.

01:46.280 --> 01:49.681
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

01:49.683 --> 01:53.252
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

01:53.254 --> 01:54.786
♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

01:54.788 --> 01:57.689
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

01:57.691 --> 01:59.892
♪ We built the Wall ♪
♪ <i>We built the pyramids</i> ♪

01:59.894 --> 02:02.561
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

02:02.563 --> 02:04.396
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

02:04.398 --> 02:04.978
♪ <i>Bang!</i> ♪

02:04.979 --> 02:08.979
<b><font color="#00FF00">♪ The Big Bang Theory 10x18 ♪</font></b>
