Original

02:08.979 --> 02:15.380
== sync, corrected by <font color="#00FF00">elderman</font> ==
<font color="#00FFFF">@elder_man</font>

02:18.684 --> 02:20.217
Hello.

02:20.219 --> 02:25.489
Hey, uh, so we've been talking,
and if you need a place to stay,

02:25.491 --> 02:28.325
we'd be happy to fix up
the garage for you.

02:28.327 --> 02:30.194
That would be amazing!

02:30.196 --> 02:32.463
I was literally just looking
at my moving boxes,

02:32.465 --> 02:35.199
trying to pick one to live in.

02:35.201 --> 02:37.034
I know it's not ideal,

02:37.036 --> 02:39.136
but you'd have plenty of space
for your furniture,

02:39.138 --> 02:40.638
and there's this cool button

02:40.640 --> 02:43.841
that makes an entire wall
go up and down.

02:43.843 --> 02:46.076
I cannot thank you enough.

02:46.078 --> 02:48.078
It is our pleasure.

02:48.080 --> 02:49.914
Hey, can you hold on one sec?

02:49.916 --> 02:51.148
Hello?

02:51.150 --> 02:53.784
Hey, buddy, you still
looking for a place to live?

02:53.786 --> 02:55.719
Uh... yeah.

02:55.721 --> 02:57.721
Why do you ask?

02:57.723 --> 02:59.423
You know, we have
the extra bedroom,

02:59.425 --> 03:01.058
and if you need it, it's yours.

03:01.060 --> 03:03.594
Oh, my God, that's so generous!

03:03.596 --> 03:04.828
It's the least we can do.

03:04.830 --> 03:06.096
I-I really appreciate it.

03:06.098 --> 03:09.700
Uh, can you hold on one second?

03:09.702 --> 03:13.804
Hey, so, Howard, what's the
bathroom situation gonna be?

03:13.806 --> 03:16.740
Well, there's a sink out there--

03:16.742 --> 03:20.210
that takes care
of half your problems.

03:20.212 --> 03:22.446
But I can use
the downstairs bathroom, right?

03:22.448 --> 03:26.283
Yeah. We barely use it,
so it'll be like it's yours.

03:26.285 --> 03:27.384
Cool, cool, yeah.

03:27.386 --> 03:29.620
Yeah, hold on one second.
Wh...?

03:29.622 --> 03:32.690
Hey, what's it like
sharing a bathroom with Penny?

03:32.692 --> 03:34.425
Is there hair everywhere?

03:34.427 --> 03:37.461
Does she use your loofah?

03:37.463 --> 03:38.862
I don't have a loofah.

03:38.864 --> 03:40.397
Okay, well, if I move in,
you can't use mine.

03:40.399 --> 03:41.598
Hold on a second.

03:43.169 --> 03:47.404
Hey, Howard, uh,
how's the Wi-Fi in the garage?

03:47.406 --> 03:48.706
I don't know.

03:48.708 --> 03:50.841
Why are you asking
all these questions?

03:50.843 --> 03:53.010
Well, to be honest,
Leonard's on the other line,

03:53.012 --> 03:55.245
and he offered me
their spare bedroom.

03:55.247 --> 03:57.247
Great! Go live there.

03:57.249 --> 04:00.250
But you made the garage
sound so fun.

04:00.252 --> 04:02.353
I just didn't want you
to feel bad about it.

04:02.355 --> 04:04.121
Unless Leonard's apartment
also has a raccoon

04:04.123 --> 04:07.424
that chews its way in
on cold nights, go there!

04:07.426 --> 04:09.760
One second.

04:09.762 --> 04:12.062
Okay, I think we're close.

04:12.064 --> 04:15.366
How do you feel about
a mini-fridge in my room?

04:15.368 --> 04:17.468
Hey, pal, you want
to live here or not?

04:17.470 --> 04:19.803
Oh, uh, hi, Penny. Yes, please.

04:21.940 --> 04:23.640
Hey.
Hi.

04:23.642 --> 04:26.276
Uh, Penny, this circular
is addressed to "occupant,"

04:26.278 --> 04:27.845
but with our
apartment switch,

04:27.847 --> 04:29.613
it's unclear whether
it's yours or mine.

04:29.615 --> 04:30.748
What's it for?

04:30.750 --> 04:31.949
Roofing.

04:31.951 --> 04:34.284
Yeah, it's yours.

04:34.286 --> 04:36.420
Okay, thanks.

04:36.422 --> 04:38.455
"Just throw it out."

04:39.592 --> 04:42.493
Speaking of occupants,
I'm given to understand

04:42.495 --> 04:45.095
Raj will be moving
into my old room.

04:45.097 --> 04:46.397
Yeah, for a little while.

04:46.399 --> 04:47.831
What about his dog?

04:47.833 --> 04:49.967
She'll be in her crate;
it's not a big deal.

04:49.969 --> 04:51.368
I suppose that's
acceptable.

04:51.370 --> 04:53.170
Well, Sheldon's getting
a little better with dogs.

04:53.172 --> 04:57.174
He even took a picture
with Pluto at Disneyland.

04:57.176 --> 05:00.377
If real dogs gave me buttons,
I'd like them, too.

05:01.547 --> 05:03.414
Well, I think it's very nice

05:03.416 --> 05:05.315
that you're helping out
our friend.

05:05.317 --> 05:07.818
I think it's nice that you're
taking whatever medication

05:07.820 --> 05:09.887
Amy's clearly giving you.

05:11.657 --> 05:13.090
And what is that
supposed to mean?

05:13.092 --> 05:14.425
Well, it's like
that science thing.

05:14.427 --> 05:17.127
For every action,
you have a gigantic

05:17.129 --> 05:20.431
and annoying reaction.

05:20.433 --> 05:22.633
Just when I thought
you couldn't get any hotter.

05:22.635 --> 05:25.069
Mm-hmm.

05:25.071 --> 05:27.604
If you're implying
that I'd have some problem

05:27.606 --> 05:29.907
with him moving into my room,
you're wrong.

05:29.909 --> 05:32.609
Raj is in a difficult
financial situation,

05:32.611 --> 05:34.912
and I'm glad that he's
making changes to improve it.

05:34.914 --> 05:37.414
Do not adjust the dosage.
You nailed it.

05:40.653 --> 05:42.219
Don't listen to them.

05:42.221 --> 05:43.887
What's weird is
that Penny almost got

05:43.889 --> 05:46.990
a science fact right.

05:46.992 --> 05:49.293
I mean, it's unfair; people just
assume I'm going to be upset

05:49.295 --> 05:51.395
by Raj moving into my old room.

05:51.397 --> 05:53.263
But you are, aren't you?

05:53.265 --> 05:54.498
Oh, I'm outraged.

05:55.768 --> 05:58.035
Talk to me.
Tell me what's going on.

05:58.037 --> 06:01.672
Well, that's been my room
since before I met Leonard,

06:01.674 --> 06:02.973
and now someone else

06:02.975 --> 06:04.341
is going to be living in it.

06:04.343 --> 06:05.709
And that someone else is not me.

06:05.711 --> 06:08.078
And you know how I feel about
people who aren't me.

06:10.282 --> 06:12.983
There are a lot of memories
wrapped up in that room.

06:12.985 --> 06:14.284
For me, too.

06:14.286 --> 06:16.753
The first time you told me
you loved me was in that room.

06:16.755 --> 06:17.855
Wrong.

06:17.857 --> 06:20.624
We were standing outside
my room in the hallway.

06:20.626 --> 06:24.194
And there is the love
of which I speak.

06:24.196 --> 06:25.929
I realize it's irrational,

06:25.931 --> 06:29.233
but with Raj moving in there,
I'm feeling a bit replaced.

06:29.235 --> 06:32.202
Well, this isn't an
easy time for him.

06:32.204 --> 06:35.706
He's losing his
apartment, he's in debt,

06:35.708 --> 06:36.974
he's probably humiliated.

06:36.976 --> 06:38.942
Yes, probably.

06:38.944 --> 06:43.113
But until we know for sure,
how can I feel better?

06:44.250 --> 06:46.583
Can I get anyone
anything at all?

06:46.585 --> 06:48.051
Raj, you don't
have to serve us.

06:48.053 --> 06:50.787
It's the least I can do for
helping me carry my stuff up.

06:50.789 --> 06:52.723
It was really no problem.

06:52.725 --> 06:55.492
Not for you,
Box of Towels.

06:57.062 --> 06:58.829
Anyway, thanks again.

06:58.831 --> 06:59.963
Hey, look at that.

06:59.965 --> 07:01.598
You've got a Raj,
we've got a Stuart.

07:01.600 --> 07:03.600
Maybe we should take them
both to the park

07:03.602 --> 07:06.937
and let them
run around together.

07:06.939 --> 07:09.940
I don't know.
Yours looks like he has worms.

07:11.677 --> 07:12.910
You ready to go?

07:12.912 --> 07:14.144
All set.

07:14.146 --> 07:15.145
What's that?

07:15.147 --> 07:18.048
A housewarming gift for Raj.

07:18.050 --> 07:20.017
Well, a bunch of fake snakes
better not

07:20.019 --> 07:23.887
spring out of it, 'cause that
was a lousy anniversary present.

07:23.889 --> 07:25.722
It's nothing like that.

07:25.724 --> 07:27.291
I just, I thought
about Raj's situation,

07:27.293 --> 07:29.793
and I had a
change of heart.

07:29.795 --> 07:31.495
You know, and
regarding your gift,

07:31.497 --> 07:34.431
you said "surprise me,"
and, boy, did I.

07:37.002 --> 07:38.135
- Hello.
- Hey. - Hi.

07:38.137 --> 07:39.636
Perfect timing.
Food's ready.

07:39.638 --> 07:41.638
Uh, wait-- before we eat,
I have a little

07:41.640 --> 07:43.807
"welcome to the building"
gift for Raj.

07:43.809 --> 07:45.242
Wait, is anything
gonna jump out...

07:45.244 --> 07:46.476
No. I already asked.

07:47.947 --> 07:50.547
Thank you, Sheldon.

07:50.549 --> 07:52.849
It's a...
blank notebook.

07:52.851 --> 07:55.419
Well, I had some of
my best ideas in that room,

07:55.421 --> 07:57.321
and I'm sure you will, too.

07:57.323 --> 07:58.889
He also never
had sex in that room.

07:58.891 --> 08:00.724
That's something else
to look forward to.

08:03.229 --> 08:04.561
This means a lot.

08:04.563 --> 08:06.863
Well, I know this is
a difficult time for you.

08:06.865 --> 08:09.499
Y-You're losing your apartment,
you're in debt,

08:09.501 --> 08:11.368
and you just--
you must be humiliated.

08:11.370 --> 08:12.169
Sheldon...

08:12.171 --> 08:13.604
Oh, good grief.

08:13.606 --> 08:15.706
She is such a stickler
for citing sources.

08:15.708 --> 08:17.574
Those were Amy's words.

08:17.576 --> 08:19.610
Sheldon...

08:19.612 --> 08:20.844
I know, I know!

08:20.846 --> 08:23.513
"Good grief" was originally said
by Charlie Brown, geez.

08:24.683 --> 08:26.650
You're right,
I am humiliated.

08:26.652 --> 08:28.118
Thanks for
pointing it out.

08:28.120 --> 08:29.720
You're such a jerk.

08:30.289 --> 08:31.622
Can you believe this guy?

08:31.624 --> 08:34.157
Yes.

08:34.159 --> 08:37.126
I-I thought that was
gonna break the other way.

08:37.129 --> 08:38.361
Come on, Sheldon.

08:38.364 --> 08:39.863
Maybe we should just
eat at our place.

08:39.865 --> 08:40.865
Fine.

08:41.500 --> 08:42.765
You took my room.

08:42.768 --> 08:44.434
You turned my friends
against me.

08:44.436 --> 08:45.535
I hope you're happy.

08:45.537 --> 08:46.970
What do I have
to be happy about?

08:46.972 --> 08:47.971
My life's a wreck.

08:47.973 --> 08:49.906
How come he can say it
and I can't?

08:49.908 --> 08:51.875
Just keep walking.

