09:01.404 --> 09:02.703
Hello, Sheldon.

09:02.705 --> 09:04.571
What a pleasant surprise.

09:04.573 --> 09:06.040
How are you?

09:06.042 --> 09:08.275
Honestly, I've been better.

09:08.277 --> 09:09.710
Do you have time?

09:09.712 --> 09:11.946
Leonard says you're very busy
these days.

09:11.948 --> 09:14.515
Oh, I just say that
because he prattles.

09:15.785 --> 09:17.484
What's going on?

09:17.486 --> 09:21.555
Well, our friend Raj
moved into my old room,

09:21.557 --> 09:25.159
and it's brought up a lot of
negative feelings for me.

09:25.161 --> 09:29.096
Mm. Well, what do you think the
loss of your room represents?

09:29.098 --> 09:31.332
Beverly, you know I
hold you in high esteem.

09:31.334 --> 09:34.601
Can we skip the part where you
pretend not to know the answer,

09:34.603 --> 09:37.104
and get to the part
where you tell me the answer?

09:37.106 --> 09:39.907
Very well, but, uh,
if you don't mind,

09:39.909 --> 09:41.976
I'd still like to pause
for effect.

09:43.312 --> 09:45.279
Now...

09:46.916 --> 09:50.317
You've recently moved in
with Dr. Fowler, yes?

09:50.319 --> 09:52.386
I have.

09:52.388 --> 09:55.522
Clearly, your old room
represents an escape hatch,

09:55.524 --> 09:57.591
and without it,
you're forced to confront

09:57.593 --> 09:59.827
the terrifying reality
of being trapped

09:59.829 --> 10:02.963
in a relationship
with Amy forever.

10:04.400 --> 10:05.766
I hadn't thought about that.

10:05.768 --> 10:08.402
And don't start
thinking about it now!

10:08.404 --> 10:11.372
Hello, Amy.

10:11.374 --> 10:14.341
Your defensiveness may indicate
similar insecurities

10:14.343 --> 10:16.910
about your relationship
with Sheldon.

10:16.912 --> 10:17.911
That's not true!

10:17.913 --> 10:20.748
She said defensively.

10:20.750 --> 10:23.784
This isn't about
me and Sheldon.

10:23.786 --> 10:27.054
This is about Rajesh moving in
with Leonard and Penny.

10:27.056 --> 10:29.223
Interesting.

10:29.225 --> 10:32.993
They've found a need
to take yet another roommate.

10:32.995 --> 10:36.697
Seems they're avoiding
some harsh realities themselves.

10:36.699 --> 10:38.632
I had no idea

10:38.634 --> 10:41.101
all our relationships
were such a disaster.

10:41.103 --> 10:42.736
Boy, you're good.

10:42.738 --> 10:45.105
That is the word
on the street, dear.

10:47.910 --> 10:50.744
Maybe moving in
was a bad idea.

10:50.746 --> 10:53.147
I haven't been here one day,
I'm already causing problems.

10:53.149 --> 10:55.182
You didn't do anything.
It's Sheldon.

10:55.184 --> 10:56.884
"You didn't do anything.
It's Sheldon."

10:56.886 --> 10:59.887
That'd make a nice
needlepoint pillow.

11:00.756 --> 11:02.956
So, relax.
We're happy to have you.

11:02.958 --> 11:04.358
Thank you, but how do I know

11:04.360 --> 11:05.893
you're not saying that
just to be nice?

11:05.895 --> 11:07.661
Do you actually pay
for that haircut?

11:07.663 --> 11:09.063
That'll do it.

11:10.866 --> 11:13.567
Hey, Raj,
I owe you an apology.

11:13.569 --> 11:16.470
Look, could you please
put your dog on a leash?

11:16.472 --> 11:18.472
Sheldon, she's fine.

11:18.474 --> 11:20.107
Well, then at least
hold her still

11:20.109 --> 11:21.542
so I can pretend she's stuffed.

11:22.411 --> 11:26.046
Raj, I let my emotions
get the best of me,

11:26.048 --> 11:28.248
and I unfairly
took it out on you.

11:28.250 --> 11:30.117
Thank you. I appreciate that.

11:30.119 --> 11:31.652
No, I can't take all the credit.

11:31.654 --> 11:34.288
I spoke with Leonard's mother,
and she made me feel better.

11:34.290 --> 11:38.158
I don't know who you talked to,
but that wasn't my mother.

11:39.995 --> 11:43.230
Beverly pointed out that
I'm experiencing insecurities

11:43.232 --> 11:44.898
in my relationship with Amy,

11:44.900 --> 11:47.935
in the same way that Leonard and
Penny are in their relationship.

11:47.937 --> 11:51.305
What are you talking about?
We're fine.

11:51.307 --> 11:53.674
Yes, you're fine
as long as you have a buffer

11:53.676 --> 11:56.043
living with you to distract
from your marital problems.

11:56.045 --> 11:57.678
It used to be me.

11:57.680 --> 12:00.447
Now it's Raj
and his attack Tribble.

12:01.617 --> 12:04.618
Anyway, I'm sorry
for everything.

12:04.620 --> 12:07.121
Oh, and FYI-- if you cry
while they're fighting,

12:07.123 --> 12:08.589
they'll take you to McDonald's.

12:15.831 --> 12:17.097
Hello, Leonard.

12:17.099 --> 12:19.800
Why are you saying
we have marital problems?

12:19.802 --> 12:21.568
We don't have marital problems!

12:21.570 --> 12:25.472
I see. You must be yelling at me
out of wedded bliss.

12:28.577 --> 12:31.378
Look, just because we took
our friend in does not mean

12:31.380 --> 12:33.480
that Penny and I are
afraid to be alone.

12:33.482 --> 12:36.583
Yeah, this is a
special circumstance.

12:36.585 --> 12:38.485
Sheldon mentioned
you tried to get your brother

12:38.487 --> 12:39.853
to live with you, as well.

12:39.855 --> 12:42.823
Yeah, well, a circumstance
can happen twice

12:42.825 --> 12:45.492
and still be special.

12:45.494 --> 12:46.927
Do you agree with that?

12:46.929 --> 12:49.329
Well, now that
you point it out...

12:49.331 --> 12:51.131
Are you kidding me?

12:51.133 --> 12:53.534
We do seem to keep
finding roommates.

12:53.536 --> 12:55.569
Now you're
taking her side?

12:55.571 --> 12:58.505
Dear, I would never come
between you and Leonard.

12:58.507 --> 13:02.075
That's for your parade
of roommates to do.

13:04.647 --> 13:08.382
Howard?

13:08.384 --> 13:09.750
Howard!

13:11.921 --> 13:13.854
It's me!
It's just me!

13:13.856 --> 13:16.223
What are you doing here?!

13:16.225 --> 13:18.659
Well, I texted you,
but you didn't respond.

13:18.661 --> 13:20.294
Leonard and Penny
were arguing...

13:20.296 --> 13:22.095
Not on my watch!

13:24.667 --> 13:26.500
It's fine.
It's just Raj.

13:26.502 --> 13:28.902
You can hit him with
the bat, but it's fine.

13:29.972 --> 13:32.906
And if my heart stops,
just let me go.

13:32.908 --> 13:34.308
I'm sorry, guys.

13:34.310 --> 13:37.077
Sheldon was upset,
Leonard and Penny were fighting.

13:37.079 --> 13:40.147
I just wanted to go someplace
where I wasn't causing problems.

13:40.149 --> 13:41.949
I'll say it again.

13:41.951 --> 13:44.151
India.

13:46.755 --> 13:49.556
Can I just stay in the garage?

13:49.558 --> 13:51.525
Don't do that. We'll make
up the couch for you

13:51.527 --> 13:52.926
and figure out something
in the morning.

13:52.928 --> 13:54.027
Thank you.

13:54.029 --> 13:55.462
Come on,
I'll get you some sheets.

13:55.464 --> 13:57.631
Then we'll see
if I can beat my high score

13:57.633 --> 13:59.066
on the blood pressure machine.

14:03.138 --> 14:06.406
Never should've had all
these kids so close together.

14:17.686 --> 14:19.353
You okay?

14:19.355 --> 14:21.722
I can't sleep.

14:21.724 --> 14:24.124
What's wrong?

14:24.126 --> 14:26.093
Beverly believes

14:26.095 --> 14:30.163
I unconsciously consider
my old room an escape hatch.

14:30.165 --> 14:32.432
Is that bothering you?

14:32.434 --> 14:35.702
Yes. I don't care for
unconscious thoughts.

14:35.704 --> 14:37.371
My brain and I
are best friends.

14:37.373 --> 14:39.773
It should tell
me everything.

14:39.775 --> 14:42.909
I mean, how it relates
to our relationship,

14:42.911 --> 14:46.346
not the bromance
between you and your brain.

14:46.348 --> 14:49.283
What if she's correct?

14:49.285 --> 14:51.852
Doesn't that say something
troubling about us?

14:51.854 --> 14:53.587
I don't know.

14:53.589 --> 14:55.789
I just think
you're the kind of person

14:55.791 --> 14:58.191
who likes a contingency plan.

14:58.193 --> 15:00.761
That is true.

15:00.763 --> 15:02.929
Did you know
I figured out

15:02.931 --> 15:05.198
in which order I would
eat all my friends

15:05.200 --> 15:07.567
in the event of
an apocalypse?

15:09.405 --> 15:12.506
You need to stop hanging out
with your brain so much.

15:12.508 --> 15:14.174
It's not a good influence.

15:18.247 --> 15:19.613
If you're looking
for spare change,

15:19.615 --> 15:21.381
I already cleaned it out.

15:23.485 --> 15:25.552
Well...

15:25.554 --> 15:28.055
Didn't think this is
where my life would be.

15:28.057 --> 15:30.924
Me, either. I'm in a bedroom
and you're on a couch.

15:30.926 --> 15:33.960
I'm actually winning.

15:33.962 --> 15:35.462
You know, we're both
down on our luck.

15:35.464 --> 15:37.564
Maybe you and I should try
to get a place together.

15:37.566 --> 15:39.833
Okay, listen to me.

15:43.505 --> 15:46.173
There is no reason
to leave here.

15:46.175 --> 15:48.108
This is great.
Everyone's nice.

15:48.110 --> 15:49.476
It's comfortable.

15:49.478 --> 15:53.213
If all goes according to plan,
this is my retirement home.

15:53.215 --> 15:54.815
Wouldn't you feel better
about yourself

15:54.817 --> 15:55.949
if you were more independent?

15:55.951 --> 15:58.051
Better than I feel
in their steam shower?

15:58.053 --> 16:00.220
I don't think so.

16:00.989 --> 16:04.024
Penny would be
the entree.

16:06.495 --> 16:09.763
Then Leonard's basically
a cheese course.

16:09.765 --> 16:13.367
And because I love
you, you're dessert.

16:13.369 --> 16:16.236
I want to say "aw,"

16:16.238 --> 16:18.438
but I'm gonna say "ew."

16:19.608 --> 16:21.708
No, you see,
I'm doing this

16:21.710 --> 16:24.177
so I can stop being
spoiled and, you know,

16:24.179 --> 16:26.580
grow as a person.

16:26.582 --> 16:28.115
Good for you.

16:28.117 --> 16:31.084
This sandwich has six dollars
worth of ham in it.

16:33.922 --> 16:37.491
Don't you even feel a little
bad sponging off your friends?

16:37.493 --> 16:40.060
Hey, look,
I went to art college,

16:40.062 --> 16:42.329
I tried to make it
as a graphic artist,

16:42.331 --> 16:43.897
a comic book artist,

16:43.899 --> 16:45.899
and you know what I got
for my efforts?

16:45.901 --> 16:47.601
A visible rib cage.

16:47.603 --> 16:49.903
I'm not kidding.

16:49.905 --> 16:52.305
You could see my heart beating.

16:52.307 --> 16:54.741
Well, no offense, but
I didn't go to art school.

16:54.743 --> 16:56.910
I have a PhD in
astrophysics.

16:56.912 --> 16:59.546
Oh, great, it'll be easier
for you to look up at the stars

16:59.548 --> 17:01.715
without a roof over your head.

17:04.420 --> 17:05.752
Morning.

17:05.753 --> 17:07.654
Did you know
Raj moved out last night?

17:07.656 --> 17:09.455
What? Why?

17:09.458 --> 17:12.058
"Leonard and Penny, I'm sorry
for all the trouble I've caused.

17:12.060 --> 17:13.527
"I went to stay at Howard's.

17:13.529 --> 17:15.395
"P.S., Cinnamon's with me,

17:15.396 --> 17:17.230
"but if you feel like
messing with Sheldon,

17:17.232 --> 17:19.833
tell him she's loose
in the building."

17:22.037 --> 17:23.703
I feel terrible.

17:23.704 --> 17:25.005
Should we go bring him back?

17:25.007 --> 17:26.239
Well, you're
the one worried

17:26.241 --> 17:28.508
having someone live with us
is a sign of problems.

17:28.510 --> 17:31.711
Oh, that was just because
my mother got in my head.

17:31.713 --> 17:35.015
It's like being possessed,
but instead of Satan, it's--

17:35.017 --> 17:37.451
Actually, it's the same thing.

17:38.454 --> 17:40.854
All right, so we'll
ask him to come back.

17:40.856 --> 17:42.956
Well, great.

17:42.958 --> 17:44.858
Don't you want
to get dressed first?

17:44.860 --> 17:46.460
Just one second.

17:52.201 --> 17:55.035
Help! Cinnamon's loose
in the building!

17:56.271 --> 17:58.472
Amy, quick, lock the door!

18:02.678 --> 18:05.011
We're so sorry if we made you
feel uncomfortable.

18:05.013 --> 18:06.680
We really weren't
fighting about you.

18:06.682 --> 18:09.015
I just never want to be
a burden on my friends.

18:09.017 --> 18:10.951
Me, either.
Don't want to be a burden.

18:10.953 --> 18:13.220
Hey, is that the baby?
I'll go check.

18:13.222 --> 18:14.821
You are not a burden,

18:14.823 --> 18:17.624
and we want you to come
back and stay with us.

18:17.626 --> 18:19.025
But I also upset Sheldon,

18:19.027 --> 18:21.461
and he's not gonna want
to come over if I'm there.

18:21.463 --> 18:24.064
More reasons
for you to stay.

18:25.367 --> 18:27.300
Halley's fine.

18:27.302 --> 18:30.203
You know she's at
my parents' house, right?

18:32.007 --> 18:35.008
And she's having
the time of her life.

18:35.911 --> 18:38.378
If you ever want
to change things up,

18:38.380 --> 18:40.280
you're always
welcome here.

18:40.282 --> 18:43.717
Just not in our bedroom,
you dumbass.

18:45.721 --> 18:48.355
I appreciate it, but I think

18:48.357 --> 18:51.258
staying with Leonard and Penny
makes more sense for everyone.

18:51.260 --> 18:53.126
Then it's settled.
And just so you know,

18:53.128 --> 18:54.160
it's only temporary.

18:54.162 --> 18:55.795
I'm not gonna get
too comfortable.

18:55.797 --> 18:57.030
Good.

18:57.032 --> 18:59.866
Nobody needs a mooch living
in their house forever.

18:59.868 --> 19:02.569
Hey, that's no way
to talk about your baby.

19:13.545 --> 19:16.079
You know what?
I'm proud of us.

19:16.081 --> 19:18.615
Yeah, with Penny and
Leonard taking in Raj,

19:18.617 --> 19:20.784
and Stuart living with
Howard and Bernadette,

19:20.786 --> 19:22.919
we're the only couple
of our social group

19:22.921 --> 19:24.754
who doesn't need
to fill the holes

19:24.756 --> 19:27.257
in their relationship
with a third party.

19:27.259 --> 19:28.825
Yup, we're killin' it.

